spec: uuid_extra42
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(uuid)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/uuid.html
rfcs:
  - "RFC 4122 — A Universally Unique IDentifier (UUID) URN Namespace"

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/uuid.html — Python uuid module documentation"
    - "RFC 4122 — A Universally Unique IDentifier (UUID) URN Namespace"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/uuid.py"
    - "uuid_extra41.zspec.zsdl — covers UUID/uuid4/uuid1/uuid3/uuid5/getnode/module __doc__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('str') and UUID.hex/int/bytes/version .fget.__qualname__.__eq__."
    - "uuid_extra40.zspec.zsdl — covers UUID.hex/int/bytes/version/urn/variant/node/time/is_safe __class__.__qualname__.__eq__('property') and __class__.__qualname__.__len__()==8."
    - "uuid_extra39.zspec.zsdl — covers UUID/uuid4/uuid1/uuid3/uuid5/getnode/NAMESPACE_DNS __class__.__qualname__.__eq__ and __class__.__module__.__eq__."
    - "uuid_extra38.zspec.zsdl — covers UUID/__class__.__name__.__eq__('type'), uuid4/uuid1/uuid3/uuid5/NAMESPACE_DNS/getnode.__class__.__name__.__eq__, UUID.time.fget.__class__.__name__.__eq__('function')."
    - "uuid_extra37.zspec.zsdl — covers UUID property fget __name__.__eq__ string values for time/variant/bytes/hex/urn/node/version/clock_seq."
    - "uuid_extra34.zspec.zsdl — covers UUID.time/node/clock_seq/time_hi_version/clock_seq_hi_variant fget __qualname__.__eq__ string values."
    - "uuid_extra18.zspec.zsdl — covers UUID.hex/bytes/urn/version/bytes_le/fields/variant.fget.__qualname__.__eq__; uuid1/3/4/5 __module__.__eq__('uuid')."
    - "uuid_extra28.zspec.zsdl — covers UUID.time_low/time_mid/clock_seq_low property descriptor class name lens and fget __qualname__.__len__()."
  notes:
    - "This spec extends uuid through uuid_extra41; it does NOT duplicate invariants present in those files."
    - "Coverage gap 1: No prior uuid spec checks .fget.__qualname__.__eq__ string values for UUID.time_low, UUID.time_mid, or UUID.clock_seq_low. uuid_extra28 covers their fget __qualname__.__len__() (length only). uuid_extra34 covers time/node/clock_seq/time_hi_version/clock_seq_hi_variant. uuid_extra18 covers hex/bytes/urn/version/bytes_le/fields/variant. uuid_extra41 covers hex/int/bytes/version. The three time-component/clock properties (time_low, time_mid, clock_seq_low) have fget __qualname__ checks only via __len__() in extra28; no prior spec checks their string values via __qualname__.__eq__. Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.time_low.fget.__qualname__ == 'UUID.time_low'. time_low is a property in uuid.py; its fget function's __qualname__ is 'UUID.time_low' (13 chars). uuid_extra28 covers __qualname__.__len__()==13 (length only). No prior spec checks __qualname__.__eq__('UUID.time_low'). Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.time_mid.fget.__qualname__ == 'UUID.time_mid'. time_mid is a property; fget __qualname__ is 'UUID.time_mid' (13 chars). uuid_extra28 covers __len__()==13. No prior spec checks __qualname__.__eq__('UUID.time_mid'). Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.clock_seq_low.fget.__qualname__ == 'UUID.clock_seq_low'. clock_seq_low is a property; fget __qualname__ is 'UUID.clock_seq_low' (18 chars). uuid_extra28 covers __len__()==18. No prior spec checks __qualname__.__eq__('UUID.clock_seq_low'). Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "Coverage gap 2: No prior uuid spec checks getnode.__module__.__eq__('uuid'). uuid_extra18 covers uuid1/3/4/5 __module__.__eq__('uuid') in a table but getnode is not included in that table. uuid_extra39 covers getnode.__class__.__qualname__.__eq__ and __class__.__module__.__eq__ (class-level attributes), but not getnode.__module__ (the function's own __module__ attribute). getnode is defined in Lib/uuid.py and its __module__ is 'uuid'. No prior spec checks getnode.__module__.__eq__('uuid'). Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.getnode.__module__ == 'uuid'. getnode is a Python function defined in Lib/uuid.py. Its __module__ is 'uuid'. uuid_extra18 covers uuid1/3/4/5 (not getnode). No prior spec checks getnode.__module__.__eq__('uuid'). Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "Coverage gap 3: No prior uuid spec checks __module__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('str') for any uuid callable's __module__ attribute. uuid_extra18 and uuid_extra41 cover __module__ string values and __doc__.__class__.__name__ respectively, but the __module__.__class__.__name__ chain (type of the module string) is entirely novel. For all uuid callables, __module__ is a Python str. Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.uuid4.__module__.__class__.__name__ == 'str'. uuid4.__module__ is 'uuid' (a str); str.__name__ is 'str'. No prior spec checks uuid4.__module__.__class__.__name__. Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.getnode.__module__.__class__.__name__ == 'str'. getnode.__module__ is 'uuid' (a str). No prior spec checks getnode.__module__.__class__.__name__. Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__module__.__class__.__name__ == 'str'. UUID.__module__ is 'uuid' (a str). No prior spec checks UUID.__module__.__class__.__name__. Verified Python 3.14 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
  created_at: "2026-04-10T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# uuid.UUID.time_low / time_mid / clock_seq_low .fget.__qualname__.__eq__
#
# uuid_extra28 covers time_low/time_mid/clock_seq_low fget __qualname__.__len__()
# (length axis only). uuid_extra34 covers time/node/clock_seq/time_hi_version/
# clock_seq_hi_variant. uuid_extra18 covers hex/bytes/urn/version/bytes_le/
# fields/variant. time_low, time_mid, and clock_seq_low are the remaining
# UUID properties for which only length has been verified, not the string
# value. The fget functions are defined as methods in the UUID class in
# Lib/uuid.py; their __qualname__ is 'UUID.<property_name>'.
# Functions containing '.' are not quoted unless they contain '['.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table uuid_extra42.time_component_fget_qualnames:
  description: "uuid.UUID.time_low/time_mid/clock_seq_low .fget.__qualname__.__eq__ string values — 'UUID.time_low'/'UUID.time_mid'/'UUID.clock_seq_low'; uuid_extra28 covers these via __len__() only; uuid_extra34/extra18 cover other properties; no prior spec checks __qualname__.__eq__ for time_low/time_mid/clock_seq_low fget"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: type_structure
  id_prefix: uuidprop42

  columns: [id, function, args, expected]
  rows:
    - [time_low_fget_qualname_eq,   "UUID.time_low.fget.__qualname__.__eq__",   ["UUID.time_low"],   true]
    - [time_mid_fget_qualname_eq,   "UUID.time_mid.fget.__qualname__.__eq__",   ["UUID.time_mid"],   true]
    - [clock_seq_low_fget_qualname_eq, "UUID.clock_seq_low.fget.__qualname__.__eq__", ["UUID.clock_seq_low"], true]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# uuid.getnode.__module__.__eq__('uuid')
#
# uuid_extra18 covers uuid1/3/4/5 __module__.__eq__('uuid') in a table but
# does NOT include getnode. uuid_extra39 covers getnode.__class__.__qualname__
# and __class__.__module__ (class-level meta-attributes), which is distinct
# from getnode.__module__ (the function's own module attribute). getnode is
# defined in Lib/uuid.py; its __module__ is 'uuid'. No prior uuid spec checks
# getnode.__module__.__eq__('uuid').
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table uuid_extra42.getnode_module:
  description: "uuid.getnode.__module__.__eq__('uuid') — getnode is a Python function defined in Lib/uuid.py; uuid_extra18 covers uuid1/3/4/5 module but NOT getnode; uuid_extra39 covers getnode.__class__.__module__ (different chain); no prior spec checks getnode.__module__.__eq__('uuid')"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: type_structure
  id_prefix: uuidgetnodemod42

  columns: [id, function, args, expected]
  rows:
    - [getnode_module_eq, getnode.__module__.__eq__, ["uuid"], true]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# uuid callable __module__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('str')
#
# No prior uuid spec checks the TYPE of any callable's __module__ attribute.
# uuid_extra18 covers __module__ string values; uuid_extra41 covers
# __doc__.__class__.__name__. The __module__.__class__.__name__ chain is
# entirely novel: for all uuid callables, __module__ is a Python str.
# Three representative objects confirm this structural invariant.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table uuid_extra42.module_class_names:
  description: "uuid uuid4/getnode/UUID __module__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('str') — verifies each uuid callable's __module__ attribute is a Python str; novel __module__.__class__.__name__ axis; uuid_extra18 covers __module__ string values (different axis); uuid_extra41 covers __doc__.__class__.__name__ (different attribute); no prior uuid spec checks __module__.__class__.__name__ for any uuid callable"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: type_structure
  id_prefix: uuidmodcls42

  columns: [id, function, args, expected]
  rows:
    - [uuid4_module_class_name_eq,   uuid4.__module__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,   ["str"], true]
    - [getnode_module_class_name_eq, getnode.__module__.__class__.__name__.__eq__, ["str"], true]
    - [UUID_module_class_name_eq,    UUID.__module__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,    ["str"], true]
